snippet.textDisplay: Let me share how I go from Colored dark Red hair to Blonde every year. After many trial and error. I take a color remover (not bleach) and that takes out all unwanted color leaving a yellow orange base. (wait a few days for hair to chill) Then I take an ASH blonde and put it on, I then TONE my hair with purple shampoo and lots of conditioner. at this point it should be in the blonde route from here you can then add a lighter blonde over top the ash and toned hair or highlights (i have done both) and there you go. Toning every shower is key i find to keep those brassy notes down and keep it on the cool side or use (go blonder by john freida) however that does give you more of a golden blonde. I also give my hair a small trim at the end of this process to encourage healthier hair. My haiir cant go platinum due to coloring it so much but if you can see my profile pic you can see the color result I get every time. :)

snippet.textDisplay: Brad, I need your advice. This summer I bleached my hair at home, I’m a natural blonde but I had a black box dye and I wanted it back to blonde. So I bleached my hair and it was left extremely damaged and yellow I couldn’t even leave the house with that hair. My sister took me to a hair salon and they said that they couldn’t put more bleach on it but they could tone it so it doesn’t look that yellow, so they toned and I got a haircut . So my hair was still looking yellow and I decided to dye it blue with crazy color semipermanent dye. Now it’s been 6 months and I haven’t done anything to my hair since. I got rid of the blue (it was really hard ) and now my hair is blonde but has green tones in it , the consistency of my hair when it’s wet is like chewing gum, I wash my hair twice a week and I don’t use heat on it. I don’t know what to do I really want to dye my hair my natural color which is like a 7.00/8.00 dark blonde but I’m afraid it will damage my hair more or because of the green tones it won’t come out good. Help.
